Privacy Policy — YouTube Video Analytics

Last updated: April 26, 2026

1. Introduction
YouTube Video Analytics ("we", "our", or "the app") is a free Android application that allows users to look up publicly available statistics for any YouTube video. We are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights.

2. Information We Collect
We do not collect, store, or share any personally identifiable information. Specifically:

We do not require you to create an account
We do not ask for your name, email address, or any personal details
We do not access your YouTube account or Google account
We do not collect your location data
We do not use any tracking or analytics SDKs that collect personal data
3. YouTube URLs You Enter
When you paste a YouTube video URL into the app, it is used solely to fetch publicly available video statistics (views, likes, comments) from YouTube's public data. This URL is stored locally on your device only (for your search history feature) and is never transmitted to our servers.

4. Advertising
This app displays advertisements served by Google AdMob. Google AdMob may collect certain device information and use cookies or similar technologies to serve relevant ads. This is governed by Google's Privacy Policy, which can be found at: https://policies.google.com/privacy

You can opt out of personalised ads by visiting your device's Google Settings → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalisation.

5. Third-Party Services
The app uses the following third-party services:

YouTube Data API — to fetch public video statistics. Subject to Google's Terms of Service and Privacy Policy.
Google AdMob — for displaying advertisements.
We do not share any data with any other third parties.

6. Data Storage
All data (such as your video search history) is stored locally on your device using Android's local storage. We have no access to this data. You can clear it at any time by clearing the app's data from your device settings or deleting individual history entries within the app.

7. Children's Privacy
Our app does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13. The app is rated "Everyone" and does not target children specifically.

8. Security
Since we do not collect or transmit personal data to any server, there is no risk of your personal information being compromised through our app.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with an updated "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.

